Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. When boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Quarter the @lime{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Drain the @king prawns{150%g}. Once hot, add the prawns, sliced pepper and @sliced mushrooms{180%g}. Fry until slightly charred and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Continue to stir while it cooks. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw prawns. They're cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the garlic and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @ketjap manis{50%g} and @water{50%ml} to the veg. Stir together, then add the @mangetout{80%g} and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles through the fragrant sauce and toss until well combined. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Share the sticky Thai style noodles between your #bowls{}. Sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%g} and coriander. Squeeze over some lime juice to finish. Enjoy!